The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Orissa girls best

 Chandigarh: Orissa upset title-favourites Manipur 1-0 to 

 win the third girls under-17 National Football Championship 

 here on Thursday. 

 The winner was scored by Rashmita Podh in the 44th minute. 

 Manipur dominated the game but could not breach the rival 

 defence. The result was sweet revenge for Orissa who suffered 

 defeat at the hands of Manipur in the final last year.

 McBride retires 

 Chicago: Brian McBride of the US has announced his retirement 

 from international football, bringing an end to a 13-year 

 international career that included appearances in the 1998, 

 2002 and 2006 World Cups. He scored 30 goals in 95 matches.

 Emerson deal

 Madrid: Brazilian midfielder Emerson completed his move 

 to Real Madrid from Juventus after passing a routine medical 

 on Wednesday. Emerson, who signed a three-year contract, 

 received a Madrid shirt bearing his name but without a number 

 at his presentation at the Bernabeu. 

 Ruud in Real

 Madrid: Dutch striker Ruud van Nistelrooy will join Real 

 Madrid from Manchester United on a three-year contract, 

 the Primera Liga club said on Thursday.

 Bhullar leads

 Calcutta: Gaganjeet Bhullar carded a two-under 70 on Day 

 II to take sole lead at the Royal Challenge Northern India 

 Amateur Golf Championship on Thursday. 




